# Pokeright_me
A turn-based monster battle game that feels like Pokemon, developed in Java with OOP.

## Description
This is a turn-based combat game where you play as a Monster Trainer who assembles a team of elemental monsters to battle wild monsters.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Main Features
### Core Gameplay
- Turn-based combat system - `Strategic battles against wild monsters`
- Monster team management - `Build and customize your team (up to unlimited monsters)`
- Type effectiveness system - `Water > Fire > Plant > Water (1.5x damage multiplier)`
- Credits economy - `Earn credits by defeating monsters, spend them in the shop`
- Save/Load system - `CSV-based persistence`
### Monster System
- Three elemental types: `Water, Fire, Plant`
- Monster stats: `HP, Mana, Attack Damage (mana non used yet sadly)`
- Status tracking: `Alive/Dead status, capture conditions (â‰¤30% HP)`
- Custom monster creation - `Create your own Monster (name, type)`
- Random generation - `Random stats for each monster`
### Inventory & Items
- Health Potion (10 credits) - `Heals 50 HP`
- Super Potion (50 credits) - `Heals 100 HP ` 
- Revive (150 credits) - `Revives dead monsters with 50% HP`
- Mana Potion (20 credits) - `Restores 50 Mana`
- Monster Trap (15 credits) - `Captures weaknd monsters (â‰¤30% HP, 70% success rate)`
### Shop System
- Item purchase with credits
- Pricing System
- Bulk buying support

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
## ðŸ—ï¸ Technical Architecture
### Object-Oriented Design

`Inheritance Hierarchy:`
Monster (abstract) -> parent
â”œâ”€â”€ WaterMonster -> children
â”œâ”€â”€ FireMonster
â””â”€â”€ PlantMonster

`Key Design Patterns:`
- `Encapsulation` - All monster attributes are private with controlled access
- `Polymorphism` - Damage calculation based on monster types
- `Abstraction` - Abstract Monster class prevents direct instantiation
- `Composition` - Team has-a Inventory, has-a List<Monster>
### Data Structures
- `ArrayList<Monster>` - Dynamic team size (no fixed limit)
- `HashMap<Item, Integer>` - inventory lookup by item name
- `Enum` - Type-safe monster types and items
### Exception Handling
- `GameException` - Custom exception for error handling
- `Try-catch blocks` - Prevents crashes from invalid user input
- `Validation` - All setter methods validate input
### Game Rules Enforcement
- Cannot attack if monster is dead  
- Cannot attack a dead target  
- Cannot heal at max HP  
- Cannot capture monsters with >30% HP  
- All illegal actions throw GameException  

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## How to Play
### Starting the Game
1. Launch: Run `Main.java`
2. New Game: Enter team name â†’ Receive 3 random starter monsters
3. Load Game: Continue from your last save
### Game Menu Options
`=== GAME MENU ===`
1. View Team         - See monster stats, credits, inventory
2. Battle Wild Monster - Enter combat
3. Use Item          - Heal/revive monsters outside battle
4. Shop              - Buy items with credits
5. Create Custom Monster - Design your own monster
6. Save Game         - Save progress to savegame.csv
7. Return to Main Menu

### Battle Actions
`During combat:`
- Attack - Deal damage (shows "super effective" for type advantage)
- Use Item - Heal, revive, or restore mana mid-battle
- Switch Monster - Change active fighter
- Try to Capture - Attempt to catch wild monster (needs â‰¤30% HP + Monster Trap)
- Run Away - Escape battle
### Type Effectiveness Chart
- Water > Fire -> 1.5x dmg
- Fire > Plant -> 1.5x dmg
- Plant > Water -> 1.5x dmg

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Monster Stats Example
Squirty (water) - HP: 112/120 | Mana: 65/70 | ATK: 28
Infento (fire) - HP: 95/105 | Mana: 58/62 | ATK: 22
Flopa (plant) - HP: 118/118 | Mana: 70/75 | ATK: 30
`Stat Ranges:`
- HP: 100-120 (custom monsters: 100-135)
- Mana: 50-70 (custom monsters: 50-85)
- Attack: 15-30 (custom monsters: 15-40)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Save System
File Format: `savegame.csv`

`Saved Data:`
- Team name and credits
- All monsters
- Inventory

`Example:`
csv
TEAM,MyTeam,750
WaterMonster,Squirty,95,120,60,70,28
FireMonster,Infento,0,105,0,62,22
INVENTORY,HealthPotion,3;MonsterTrap,7;


