## Special Features & Particularities
### Unique Design Choices
1. No Monster Limit
2. Custom Error Messages - Yes i will shout at you
3. Dynamic Stats - Every monster has randomized stats
4. Custom Monster Creator - Name and Type
5. Transparent Calculations - Exact numbers for everything visible
6. CSV Persistence - Editable SaveFiles
### Balance & Strategy
- Type advantage - 50% dmg boost
- Resource management - credits
- Capture mechanics - Capture = Monster, Kill = Credits
- Team composition - Balance your team with different types :D

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Technical Specifications
### OOP Applied
- Encapsulation - Private fields, controlled access  
- Inheritance - Monster hierarchy  
- Polymorphism - Type-based damage calculation  
- Abstraction - Abstract Monster class  
- Composition - Team contains Inventory & Monsters  
### Error Handling
- Never crashes on invalid input
- Custom GameException for violations and you also get verbally violated
- Validation in all setter methods
- Safe file with try-catch

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Game Rules Summary
### Combat Rules
- Turn-based: Player acts â†’ Enemy acts â†’ Repeat
- dead monsters cannot act or be targeted
- Damage is: attackDamage * typeMultiplier
### Healing Rules
- Cannot heal monsters at max HP (throws exception)
- Cannot heal dead monsters (use Revive first)
- Revive: Restores 50% max HP (bugged a bit on %hp restore)
### Economic Rules
- Start with 500 credits
- Earn 50-100 credits per battle victory
- Items cost 10-150 credits
- No credit limit

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Requirements Done
- Multiple monster species with types  
- Monster characteristics (HP, Mana, Attack)  
- Rock-Paper-Scissors type system (2x damage)  
- death mechanics (0 HP = cannot act)  
- Player team with 3 starting monsters  
- Inventory with consumables  
- Credits system  
- Combat against random monsters  
- Item usage system  
- Save/Load functionality  
- Console-based menu interface  
- Shop for purchasing items  
- OOP hierarchy (no code duplication)  
- Abstract Monster class (cannot instantiate generic)  
- Encapsulation (private attributes)  
- Polymorphic damage calculation  
- Dynamic team size (ArrayList)  
- HashMap inventory (inventory lookup)  
- Exception handling (no crashes)  
- CSV persistence (exact game state)  

